name: Unstatic Outdoor 5G NR Router OTD500
features: The OTD500 is a durable 5G outdoor router built for reliable connectivity in demanding environments.
Its IP55-rated housing withstands harsh conditions, and the integrated mounting bracket enables quick, hassle-free installation.
Dual SIM and eSIM with automatic switching provide exceptional network flexibility and redundancy.
Gigabit Ethernet ports with PoE-in and PoE-out simplify setup by combining power and data in a single cable.
Fully RMS-compatible, the OTD500 offers effortless remote management, making it perfect for outdoor connectivity solutions.

Mobile.Mobile module: 5G Sub-6Ghz SA/NSA 2.4/3.4Gbps DL (4x4 MIMO), 900/550 Mbps UL (2x2); 4G (LTE) – LTE Cat 19 1.6Gbps DL, Cat 18 200Mbps UL; 3G – 42 Mbps DL, 5.76Mbps UL
Mobile.eSIM: Consumer type eSIM, profile download and removal operations, up to 7 eSIM profiles; does not include data plans
Mobile.SIM switch: 2 SIM cards, auto-switch cases: weak signal, data limit, SMS limit, roaming, no network, network denied, data connection fail, SIM idle protection
Mobile.Status: IMSI, ICCID, operator, operator state, data connection state, network type, bandwidth, connected band, signal strength (RSSI), SINR, RSRP, RSRQ, EC/IO, RSCP, data sent/received, LAC, TAC, cell ID, ARFCN, UARFCN, EARFCN, MCC, and MNC
Mobile.SMS: SMS status, SMS configuration, EMAIL to SMS, SMS to EMAIL, SMS to HTTP, SMS to SMS, scheduled SMS, SMS autoreply, SMPP
Mobile.USSD: Supports sending and reading Unstructured Supplementary Service Data messages
Mobile.Block/Allow list: Operator block/allow list (by country or separate operators)
Mobile.Band management: Band lock, Used band status display
Mobile.SIM idle protection service: Provides the possibility to configure the router to periodically switch to the unused SIM card and establish a data connection in order to prevent the SIM card from being blocked
Mobile.SIM PIN code management: SIM PIN code management enables setting, changing, or disabling the SIM card's PIN
Mobile.Bridge: Direct connection (bridge) between mobile ISP and device on LAN
Mobile.Passthrough: Router assigns its mobile WAN IP address to another device on LAN
Mobile.Framed routing: Framed routing: support an IP network behind 5G UE

Ethernet.Ethernet: 2 x ETH ports (can be configured as WAN), 10/100/1000 Mbps, compliance with IEEE 802.3, IEEE 802.3u, 802.3az standards, supports auto MDI/MDIX crossover

Network.Routing: Static routing, Dynamic routing (BGP, OSPF v2, RIP v1/v2, EIGRP, NHRP), Policy based routing
Network.Network protocols: TCP, UDP, IPv4, IPv6, ICMP, NTP, DNS, HTTP, HTTPS, SFTP, FTP, SMTP, SSL/TLS, ARP, VRRP, PPP, PPPoE, UPNP, SSH, DHCP, Telnet, SMPP, SNMP, MQTT, Wake On Lan (WOL), VXLAN
Network.VoIP passthrough support: H.323 and SIP-alg protocol NAT helpers, allowing proper routing of VoIP packets
